{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5bc2b24b-94f8-4297-bed9-fc19b4349d35","content":"\n\nHere's what to change:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages:**\n   - Update `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it bundles Microsoft.Testing.Platform support).\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's no longer needed.\n   - Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` if you need coverage (optional).\n\n2. **Enable the new platform in your `.csproj`:**\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests with:**\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly via the generated executable:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run --project YourTests.csproj -- --help\n   ```\n\n4. **Key behavioral changes:**\n   - Each test project now produces a **standalone executable** (a test host).\n   - CLI flags differ from VSTest (e.g., `--filter` becomes `--treenode-filter`; run `-- --help` for options).\n   - `.runsettings` files are still supported but some VSTest-specific settings may need updating.\n\nNo changes to your `[Test]`, `[TestFixture]`, or other NUnit attributes are needed — only the infrastructure layer changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"538c61f1-c196-4a79-91a6-8d0e0f8ebd4a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question, not a code change request. Let me provide a concise answer based on what I know.","outputTokens":393},"id":"13679059-400b-44b8-b8d8-a49a4a3ada28","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:42:26.314Z","parentId":"819e9983-5ade-454a-8379-00dac14440c8"}
